Does this issue occur when all extensions are disabled?:
Yes, but the issue is with an [extension](https://github.com/Ventilador/vue-lang-extension) im building.


Currently the typescript language feature extension uses the [LanguageProvider](https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/blob/master/extensions/typescript-language-features/src/languageProvider.ts#L24) to register capabilities for a ts-based language from a tsserver plugin. The thing is, when creating the descriptor for the languageProvider, the [TypeScriptServiceClientHost](https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/blob/master/extensions/typescript-language-features/src/typeScriptServiceClientHost.ts#L120) hardcodes the "_typescript-plugins_" id to the descriptor, later, when the language provider gets registered, there are some language capabilities, like [completions](https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/blob/master/extensions/typescript-language-features/src/features/completions.ts#L707), [formatting](https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/blob/master/extensions/typescript-language-features/src/features/formatting.ts#L95), [implementationsCodeLens](https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/blob/master/extensions/typescript-language-features/src/features/implementationsCodeLens.ts#L100), [jsDocCompletions](https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/blob/master/extensions/typescript-language-features/src/features/jsDocCompletions.ts#L118), [referencesCodeLens](https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/blob/master/extensions/typescript-language-features/src/features/referencesCodeLens.ts#L102), [dependentRegistration](https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/blob/master/extensions/typescript-language-features/src/utils/dependentRegistration.ts#L89) and [tagClosing](https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/blob/master/extensions/typescript-language-features/src/features/tagClosing.ts#L172), that use the [ConfigurationDependentRegistration](https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/blob/master/extensions/typescript-language-features/src/utils/dependentRegistration.ts#L89), which as the name says, it registers the capability only if a certain config value is set to truthy. That config is based on the descriptors id, which is used as a main section to search the config file, it ends up doing

`vscode.workspace.getConfiguration(descriptor.id, null).get('suggest.enabled')`

where `descriptor.id` is "_typescript-plugins_".
